    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup is anchored today by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (75.69), who benefits from an elite 13% SP skill bump against Wacha, and a high-leverage spot in the order. He is joined by the top-tier efficiency of **Jung Hoo Lee** (65.65) and **Luis Arraez** (65.71), both of whom capitalize on a prime matchup against V\u00e1squez, R; the high xERA (4.91) of the opposing starter provides the necessary floor to justify aggressive starts. **Daulton Varsho** (63.11) and **Bryson Stott** (62.61) also clear the 60+ \"Strong\" threshold, buoyed by significant positive platoon adjustments. We are leaning into these favorable splits, as the aggregate xERA profile for today's slate suggests a productive day for our core offensive weapons.\n\nOur most critical bench decision involved **Gavin Sheets** (39.12), who missed the start by the narrowest of margins. Despite a positive platoon edge against McDonald, his negative SP skill interaction (-19%) and failure to eclipse our 40.0 \"Zebras\" floor rendered him a statistical liability. Elsewhere, we are exercising caution with **Tyler Freeman** (59.33); while his park factor is an elite +14%, he faces a notable risk from Brazob\u00e1n's elite 1.87s catcher pop time, which directly threatens his ability to contribute in our scarcest category, stolen bases. We are also monitoring **Will Smith** (50.73) and **Jonathan Aranda** (47.46), both of whom are facing left-handed starters; their scores are suppressed by these platoon disadvantages, but their roster slots are maintained due to the absence of superior alternatives. We remain vigilant regarding any last-minute weather shifts or defensive replacements that might necessitate a late-game pivot for the LawDog roster.",
